rComments: Sooo boring. Maybe the worst class I've taken at UofT. Expectations aren't clear. Stories she chooses such. Take another course. TAKE ANOTHER COURSE.

Professor Caskey is hands down the best instructor I have ever had, and the only one that I can honestly say GENUINELY cares about her students in and outside the classroom. I have never come across a nicer prof who goes so far out of her way to make sure you have every chance at success with the material and the course. Truly a rare gem at U of T!

A really sweet, kind and caring lady who is always willing to talk with students. However, her lectures are super rehearsed. Even during class discussions she would direct it back to her own comments. I would say the class is fairly easy. Unfortunately there are only 3 assessments (An in-class essay, an essay worth 40% and the final).

BORING but nice teacher Lectures as if reading from script, makes the whole thing very dull, although the texts themselves are interesting Caring but does not provide much intellectual stimulation Only 3 grading items with a 40% essay

Really boring lectures where she's rehearsed word for word exactly what she wants to say, very unnatural and phony. Only 3 grades so if you don't do well on one single thing, you suffer a lot. The material is generally bland and the essay questions and class discussions were not very thought provoking. Take a different English class.

Great class. Super clear lectures, very obvious about expectations and assignments especially for students who may not have taken previous English courses. Truly cares about the students, friendly, approachable, and will try to remember your name!

I loved her lectures, and she is the nicest person. I was skeptical about Canadian short fiction, but the course material was amazing and I am so glad I took this course. I would recommend it to anyone. She has amazing insights, and really makes an effort to get the class involved and to make students feel like they're making valued contributions.
I really enjoyed Professor Caskey. She is a really experienced and interested in actually teaching people, which is an essential quality for a Prof.

I loved her lectures, and found her views insightful. I had not expected much for the course, but enjoyed it immensely. Its clear she loves her job, and that makes it even more worthwhile to attend. Hands down, one of the best English classes I have taken thus far.

Caskey leads interesting, insightful discussions about the course material. Even if you don't do the reading before the lectures, they're valuable because once you revisit a story, you'll remember her analysis. She prompts students to find their own answers and begin to ask questions about texts. She's always smiling, truly passionate about English

This prof's lecturing style was clear and organized, but offered no great insight into the short stories we read. Even though I was not expecting much from this class, I came out feeling like I had completely wasted my time. She's nice, but not interesting, inquiring or provoking at all-- she runs her class sort of like a kindergarten teacher.

She is a wonderful prof. Articulate, kind, accomodating, well organized and most importantly, CLEAR about expectations. Gives lots of examples, encourages students' own ideas. Just simply amazing. Also, she is very beautiful, and always smiling. Had a great experience with her!

Really great insight, made a potentially boring class interesting.  To be honest, didn't attend many lectures and ended class with an 80% - Just read the material and you're great.  Constructive feedback.

Most English profs rant on about things and go off on unrelated tangents. She does not. She's very clear about what she wants in essays, and gives plenty of very good examples in class and posts them online. She's extremely engaging and has a very friendly demeanor. Honestly just loved everything about her! Great prof!
I didn't like her lecturing style. She basically reads of her paper half the time or puts her notes on the projector so we could read it, which is pointless. She is ineffective as a lecturer.
The class is quite boring but it is really beneficial to attend the class if you want to do well on the tests and essay. She is really nice and helpful but the lectures were realllly boring.

Caskey was overall a well-informed and intelligent professor. The lectures were interesting and informative, with a good mix of class discussion and actual lecturing on part of the prof. Assignments were graded by the TAs who were looking for a very specific kind of paper; they marked hard for a 2nd year course.

She was a wonderful teacher! The lectures were quite insightful and interesting, and she was a very approachable teacher, especially when it came to asking for help. The TA's, however, never came to the class unless it was a test day, but she more than made up for them. I would take any other class that she teaches!
She has a clear enthusiasm for subject (Canadian Short Story)
This woman has the most boring lectures I've ever attended, and the TA's mark ridiculously hard for a class with such simple lectures.
No Comments
Amazing. Intelligent. Thoughtful. Articulate. Truly one of the most amazing professors I've ever had. Remarkable.

I absolutely love this woman. I've never had a professor who was so kind, understanding, approachable, and passionate. Like some of the other comments here, she too made me want to write better for her. I'm so sad she isn't teaching any other third year classes for me to take next year. Thank you Dr. Caskey! (Take her class, you won't regret it!)

The stories and classes were good but they never ran the full time and I could have learned more. The TA's, who are unavailable, do all the marking. The marking was limited to interpretation. I got no comments on structure or anything I could improve upon. Most comments were the TA's (narrow) interpretations, which were no more valid than my own.

Extremely narrow minded in approaching text analysis and further makes incredulously far fetched conclusions at the same time. Completely useless TAs that don't even attend the lecture, and are limited to pure technical nitpicking. No academical return with very little readings given.

Amazing woman. Clear, insightful, intelligent, and so very helpful and accommodating. And the best part is that she appreciates her students' ideas, concerns, and issues as much as they appreciate her!

this woman is great. it was a class of 100 and she still made an effort to learn everyones name. she didnt discriminate against anyone, or their opinions, even if they were putting down the book. she had flexible office hours and AMAZING lectures. i was sad to leave when the class was over. if ur into english, or not, take her class.

She DOES offer office hours, if she wasn't able to make her scheduled hours she always offered alternate times that you could meet with her. Was always open to new/creative ideas as long as you could back them up with the text. She's very articulate, sharp, and rarely do you hear an "umm". A very kind woman who truly wants you to do well.

extremely articulate, clear in her expectations. In the summer course there were 3 1-hour in-class essay tests, she let us know ahead of time which text the test would be about for one, gave passage to work with for another. Actual lectures however were not very stimulating. great course for beginners.

she has her own fixed idea of the text, and is not open to new ones, does not offer office hours, and her teaching assistants are completely useless, they have no idea what's going on in the class b/c they don't  attend, other than that she is nice and easy to approach, you have to find out what she likes and just do it,no creativity allowed!
extraordinarily gracious and wonderfully articulate

My fave prof at U of T. She had organized lectures that were intelligent and thought provoking. She was well articulate and professional. Also one of the nicest people in the world. She remembers names and faces years after being in her class. A true lady and intellectual.

One of the most inspirational professors I have encountered.  I found myself wanting to write better for her.  Extremetly accesible and always willing to help out her students whenever possible.  I wanted to hug her at the end of every lecture and was a little misty at the class being over.  Amazing!

Sarah is the best prof I have ever had!!!Thanks so much for all your support this year Sarah!!!You were so supportive on an academic level and non-academic level...thank you again. :) You are an amazing prof and I hope I have another course with you soon!

For an English class, she makes an effort to include gender and colonial analysis in the book choices and class discussion. She attempts to make the material interesting, even if you don't like it, and doesn't make class manditory.
Very friendly
A lovely, kind, and generous human being.  A wonderful professor.

Professor Caskey is the gem of the English dept., and by far one of the best profs I've had in the past 4 years. The novels she chose were fascinating and brilliant, and her lectures were always engaging and interesting. Would definetely recommend taking a class with her!
excellent lecturer, beautiful person

Dr. Caskey is a fabulous professor.  She is clear and articulate, and interested in/encourages student participation.  Even if you don't enjoy the required novels, the discussion about the novels are interesting, regardless.  Definitely take one of her classes if you can.
This professor is a true rarity. Will to go out of her way to ensure that students get the most form the course. Well prepared and interactive lectures.

Dr. Caskey is an excellent prof. She's speaks clearly in lectures and takes the time to repeat important material so that students don't miss out on them. She is kind and approachable for issues such as essays and tests. What a shame that she's a sessional prof, cause she's a gem the dept must keep!

Dr.Caskey is very articulate and well spoken, never left hmming and hawing for the correct word. She has well prepared lectures and incorporates her ideas with those of the student's which are brought up in discussion. She is very approachable. And she actually remembers your name!

She is an awesome professor, who actually cares about her students.  She is so helpful, and takes the time to help students in need.  She gets the class involved in discussions, and never undermines a students comment.

She was an amazing prof! She was funny and very helpful. A lot of discussion in her classes that wasn't necessary. She never stops when students ramble on. She could have covered more of her ideas and less of the students who talked too much!
An AMAZING prof. she is so clear about the concepts and very easy going.

To respond to an earlier comment, Women's Studies is not about bashing men.  The professor does attempt to integrate gender analysis into her lectures.  That said, as a Women's Studies major I found her analysis superficial and riddled with heterosexism.
Class can descend into a Women's Studies-esque dialogue against men, but otherwise is very interesting. Readings are phenomenal. Dr. Caskey is stunningly attractive.
So nice! If you can take a class with her, go for it.
No Comments
